How can I modify this Java code to express my satisfaction with the new acquaintance I've made?
String newFriend = "John";
System.out.println("I have formed a new acquaintance with " + newFriend);

To express your satisfaction with the new acquaintance you've made, you can modify the Java code by adding a statement that conveys your feelings. Here's how you can do it:

```java
String newFriend = "John";
System.out.println("I have formed a new acquaintance with " + newFriend);
System.out.println("I am really pleased to have met " + newFriend + "! It's always great to make new friends.");
```

This added line will print a statement expressing your satisfaction with meeting your new friend.
